SENATE CHAMBER
STATE OF OKLAHOMA DISPOSITION
FLOOR AMENDMENT No. ________
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
(Date)
I move to amend Senate Bill No. 1980 as follows:
1. On Page 2, Lines 9-10, by deleting after the word “entity” on Line 9 and before the word “who”
on Line 10, all language and inserting the words “, or agent thereof,”;
2. On Page 2, Line 10, by deleting after the word “who” and before the word “gift”, the word “sells”
and inserting the word “issues”;
3. On Page 2, Line 11, by deleting after the semicolon, the word “and”;
4. On Page 2, Line 13, by inserting after the word “certificate” and before the period, the following
language:
“; and
6. “Value” means the greatest amount of economic loss the owner of the property might
reasonably suffer.”;
5. On Page 2, Line 20, by deleting after the word “card” and before the word “gift”, the word “or”
and inserting a comma;
6. On Page 2, Line 20, by inserting after the word “certificate” and before the word “shall”, the
words “, or the packaging of such items”.
